 workplace and elsewhere—she says interracial couples are at a disadvantage, which is only exacerbated by current law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aRace discriminationxLaw and legislationzUnited States. 0aTrials (Divorce)zUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030016682840uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030016688040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300166880423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300166880/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY